description:
&lt;p&gt;The ECT Team based at Ealing Hospital is looking to recruit a new Team Leader for Connolly Suite which provides the ECT (and Clozapine services) for the 3 London Boroughs (Ealing, Hammersmith and Fulham and Hounslow) which make up West London NHS Trust. The clinic provides treatment for both inpatient and community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a team made up of a range of disciplines including nurses, psychiatrists, anaesthetists, operating department practitioners and phlebotomists. The team is friendly, supportive and undertakes a range of best practice work providing training and professional development both within and external to the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The highly motivated multi-disciplinary team provide an integrated mental health service to a diverse and multi-cultural population and endeavours to reflect this in the workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ECT clinic runs two days a week at Connolly suite, however, on non-clinic days this role is required to undertake ECT assessment and post treatment care and audit. For patients with complex physical needs we are able to use the theatre facilities within Ealing Hospital to provide more supportive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role encompasses both clinical and administrative requirements including monitoring and meeting the standards required for ECTAS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is primarily to work within the ECT service and that will be the main focus. There will also be an expectation to provide support to the manager in his role within the tri-borough clozapine services and at times to deputise for him.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to lead others and influence service development is crucial in the new Team Leader. The successful candidate would have vision and drive to further develop the department within the local mental health services including some in-reach and teaching sessions to both inpatient and community teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be responsible for supporting members of the team and have excellent communication skills. You would provide support to the ECT Manager to ensure that: Supervision, Appraisal, Training and Development are up to date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide support for the team members, ensuring CQC and ECTAS standards; embedding Trust Policies and ensuring staff work within professional codes of conduct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be on-going support for mandatory training and any external courses relevant to the role&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; Specific in-house training to develop knowledge and skills within the role is delivered regularly as well as attending ECT Specialist Interest groups and external conferences. Experience in ECT is not an essential requirement for applicants as a comprehensive induction will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer a highly supportive and cohesive multi-disciplinary team both within the department and the Trust with a range of opportunities to further develop your abilities and career in an exciting speciality and friendly service. There is also the opportuinity to be fully involved in current and future research. We can offer additional training including ECT Nurse Training, ILS and pocHi training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSophie WhiteEmail addresssophie.white@westlondon.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie White: sophie.white@westlondon.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flu vaccination – what we expect from our staff&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At West London we look after patients who are vulnerable. Each year, seasonal flu affects thousands of people in the UK. Occurring mainly in winter, it is an infectious respiratory disease capable of producing symptoms ranging from those similar to the common cold, through to the very severe or even fatal disease. The wellbeing of our staff and patients is of the utmost importance to us, and it is the expectation of the Trust that all patient-facing staff have an annual flu vaccination, provided free of charge by the Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
